data.description: Perfectly priced historic home for sale in the centrally located Monon Yard neighborhood that's walking distance to the Monon Trail, the brand-new Bottleworks District, Goose the Market, the 25th and Monon development in progress, and high-quality education including The Oaks Academy and Center for Inquiry #27. The house is welcoming and one-of-a-kind with timeless character and modern updates including renovated kitchen and butler pantry with wet bar and wine fridge. Have your breath taken away by the stately foyer staircase, original trim, pocket doors, and antique fireplace with gas-line hookup. This home boasts three, separate living spaces including a sun-drenched sunroom and two living rooms. A spacious front porch adds curb appeal and plenty of opportunities for entertaining. High-end, modern light fixtures and sconces are throughout including the upstairs hall retrofitted with spotlights for an art gallery.     Tons of opportunity with this property, including the ability to double the size of the yard by purchasing the empty lot next door (MLS #21948396) that's already fenced in and landscaped with a fire pit and berms. There is potential for additional space through renovating the attic which has vaulted ceilings, a framed out bathroom, and perfect infrastructure for a master suite.    SELLERS WILLING TO CONTRIBUTE TO 2/1 BUY DOWN!
